cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of future mobile networks and their communication paradigms. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper focuses on interest-based communication in mobile social networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses protocol design philosophy and analyzing the context in which the service is to be deployed. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions interest based on web browsing and user profiles, which could involve multimedia content. 
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may touch on security and privacy concerns in interest-based communication.
